Computing Reviews
The Association for Computing Machinery (ACM) publishes Computing
Reviews, the leading review journal for literature in the computing
field.  The ACM staff scans thousands of books, proceedings, and
conference papers each year selecting the most important contributions
for candid, forthright review by specialists in all areas of computing.
Computing Reviews contains comparative reviews, assessing several
books on the same topic, evaluating them for coverage, readability
and value.  For more information on this monthly journal, 
membership in the Association for Computing Machinery (ACM)
and ACM's Publications Catalog contact ACM's Member Services Department:
